# === Google Sign-In (Supabase Auth) ===
#
# Client ID & secret live in Supabase → Authentication → Providers → Google (not in this file).
#
# Supabase → Authentication → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs — include production plus local:
#   https://app.t360.in/weblogin/
#   https://app.t360.in/weblogin
#   toastmaster360://auth/callback              (native Android/iOS OAuth return)
#   http://127.0.0.1:8765/google-auth.html          (local OAuth test: npm run local:test-web)
#   http://localhost:8765/google-auth.html
#   http://127.0.0.1:8081/weblogin/                   (Expo web dev, if you use 8081)
#   http://localhost:8081/weblogin/
#   http://127.0.0.1:8081/weblogin/**                 (wildcard if your Supabase project allows it)
#
# Google Cloud Console → OAuth client: authorized redirect URI must include Supabase’s callback, e.g.
#   https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#
# App code (web) uses redirectTo: `${window.location.origin}/weblogin/` — match those URLs above.
#
# === Sign in with Apple (Supabase Auth) ===
#
# Supabase → Authentication → Providers → Apple: add Services ID, Team ID, Key ID, and private key
# from Apple Developer (Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles). See:
#   https://supabase.com/docs/guides/auth/social-login/auth-apple
#
# Use the same Redirect URLs as Google (e.g. https://<ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback is handled by Supabase;
# your app redirectTo URLs like /weblogin/ must still be allowlisted under URL Configuration).
#
# Local web (Expo): the app sends redirectTo = http://localhost:8081/weblogin/ (or 127.0.0.1). If those are NOT in
# Supabase → URL Configuration → Redirect URLs, Auth falls back to Site URL (e.g. https://app.t360.in) after Apple —
# you will land on production instead of localhost. Add both:
#   toastmaster360://auth/callback              (native Android/iOS OAuth return)
#   http://localhost:8081/weblogin/
#   http://127.0.0.1:8081/weblogin/
#
# iOS app: enable “Sign In with Apple” capability in Xcode / EAS; for App Store, Apple requires Sign in with Apple
# if you offer other third‑party sign-in (e.g. Google).
